{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed before it could produce a fully stable library update for `org.flywaydb:flyway-core:11.14.1`, even though the coverage run itself succeeded (`43/43` dynamic-access coverage, metrics status `success`). Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1080-library-update-request-org.flywaydb-flyway-core-11.14.1-66bf2455\n\nThe most likely failing stage was generated-test stabilization across the consecutive Flyway versions, not the core coverage/metadata pass. Evidence: earlier preserved `gradle-test` runs failed in native-image execution with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` from `ClassicConfigurationTest` and `EncryptionUtilsTest`, including missing reflection for `org.flywaydb.core.internal.command.clean.CleanModel.getMode()` and a reflective `java.lang.Object` constructor; see `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:11.14.1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T20-46-47-465977Z.log`. Later runs passed after follow-up fixes (`.../gradle-test-2026-05-03T20-52-12-637765Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-05-03T20-53-18-033556Z.log`), and checkstyle also passed (`human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:11.14.1/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-03T20-55-11-632476Z.log`).\n\nThe preserved follow-up logs also point to brittle generated tests that reference Flyway internals which vary across the `10.20.1` to `11.10.4` consecutive-version window, including `ConfigUtils.getPossibleFlywayConfigurations(...)`, `ClasspathLocationHandler`, `ClassicConfiguration#getConfigurationExtension(...)`, and `FlywaySqlException.throwFlywayExceptionIfPossible(...)`; see `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:11.14.1/metadata-fix/codex.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.flywaydb:flyway-core:11.14.1/local-ci-fixup/run-consecutive-tests-2026-05-03T20-58-43-589076Z.log`.\n\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially `tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/11.14.1/src/test/java/flyway/ConfigUtilsTest.java`, `ClassicConfigurationTest.java`, `FlywaySqlExceptionTest.java`, and `src/test/java/com/ibm/flyway/ClassPathScannerTest.java`, and keep only the compatibility guards needed across the consecutive-version range.\n2. Re-run the consecutive-version gate for `org.flywaydb:flyway-core:11.14.1`, then confirm `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.flywaydb:flyway-core:11.14.1` still passes with the metadata changes.\n3. If those generated tests remain too version-specific, replace them with assertions against stable Flyway APIs while keeping the current metadata changes, which already reached full dynamic-access coverage."}}
